rComments: Fantastic prof. Yes his slides are messy, but if you pay attention in class and attend tutorials, you will know exactly what is covered on midterms and the exam. He's very knowledgeable, professional and hilarious. I learned a great deal about viruses,- he makes virology uber interesting!

Terrible professor. Lectures are extremely disorganized. He skips slides, and jumps back randomly and will go on long unrelated tangents and then gloss over the important stuff when he runs out of time. Wouldve been an interesting course but he cant teach.

Horrible, worst professor. He talks a lot about what we don't need to know and rushes through the important parts of the lecture. He is also very unprofessional during lectures and makes comments about HIV and gay men. The lecture material is actually interesting and would be fun to learn if there was a better professor teaching.

rComments: Use a recorder if you're trying to get an A. I found it extremely difficult to understand what he was saying during lecture. It wasn't due to his accent, but mainly because he would skip the majority of his slides and ramble a lot. I do not think he is professional during lectures (comments about gays and HIV) or during office hours (very rude).

Funny and enjoys what he does but EXTREMELY disorganized lectures, essentially impossible to follow. Skips many many slides that end up being on exam, can't understand him. The stuff is fascinating but his teaching is sub par at best
Very good professor, always motivates students. However you definitely need to study to do well in his class.

I have graduated from UofT over a year ago, but still remember how amazing this professor is! Very inspirational and truly cares for his students! I still remember many of the things he taught me about virology!

If you study, you will do well. He is also very generous and adjusts marks at the end of midterms and final exam.
TAKE THIS CLASS, you don't have to go to lecture as long as you have the recordings but honestly would recommend an immunology and biology background!
